  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Guatemala Volcano Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Dry food kit distribution to the displaced both in shelters and elsewhere. Household hygiene kit distribution to those in shelters</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	There are 1,702,130 people affected by the volcano eruption, many of them lost their crops of coffee, and corn
&#x2022;	The government declared a state of public calamity for three states: Escuintla, Sacatep&#xE9;quez y Chimaltenango
&#x2022;	More than 1,607 persons are displaced and staying in 4 shelters, three in Escuintla and one in Sacatep&#xE9;quez
&#x2022;	There are a lot of people staying at homes of relatives or remaining in their own homes for fear of losing their belongings.
&#x2022;	The streams of water are polluted with ashes and volcanic sand.
&#x2022;	Even though the volcano is no longer erupting the government requests the affected population to stay in shelters
&#x2022;	Non-official sources assert that 68 dead bodies have been found.</narrative>
  </description>
